 A 34-year-old man Chukwudi Chukwumezie has been arrested for allegedly defiling a 15-year-old girl in Anambra State. The suspect, who claimed to be the pastor of Mountain Zion Deliverance Ministry, Ugamuma village, Obosi, had earlier been arrested for defiling a teenager at a hotel in Obosi under pretext of carrying out a deliverance session for her. Chukwumezie was charged to court but reportedly jumped bail before he reportedly went after another teenage girl using same modus operandi. Confirming the incident, police spokesman Haruna Mohammed said the suspect would be charged to court after investigations. 